  "name": "Advanced Digital Video Post Production",
  "description": "This course provides an in-depth analysis of moving image / sound ingest and post production techniques as employed in a professional production environment. Students perform practical exercises using professional applications illustrating native video resolutions, and applied compression strategies. By identifying the parameters of file-based media, consequences of compression, practical delivery-driven workflows and specifications, the student will develop a practical foundation in professional media production tools, standards and practices. Site visits will illustrate the scale of implementation in an enterprise (Network Broadcast) environment.",
